    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down. | Bromley. | Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Oct. 19.</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>The “Mattee” is the species which you name. I am much obliged for the correction at p. 286 of the figure “713.” which is a misprint.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>I expect soon to receive the remaining clean sheets of vol 1, &amp; when rec<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> they shall be sent <hi rend="underline">without delay</hi>.<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>I shall have great pleasure in sending you a perfect copy of the book, &amp; you have the best right of any one to claim a copy.<ref target="#foot.f4"/></p>
<p>In Vol. 2. p. 181 you will find some pages which you have already translated in the last edit. of the Origin, &amp; which I have here re-inserted; but will you be so kind as to compare them carefully, as I have altered &amp; inserted a few sentences in the hope of making the subject clearer.<ref target="#foot.f5"/> I do not know what you will think about Chap. 27;<ref target="#foot.f6"/> I fear it is very wild, but after mature reflection I believe that physiologists will some day be compelled to admit some such doctrine.</p>
<p>With cordial thanks for all the kind interest you take about my book I remain | my dear Sir | yours very sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">3.2 of any one] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n2">4.6 some day] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
